body:
Updating to the new module printing syntax from https://github.com/llvm/circt/pull/6205

I'm running into an issue with `loc(unknown)` for a port, here's an example:

```mlir
module {
    hw.module @test(in %I: i1 loc(unknown), out O: i1 loc(unknown)) {
        hw.output %I : i1
    }
}
```

```
circt._mlir_libs.MLIRError: Unable to parse module assembly:
error: "-":3:5: 'hw.module' op block argument locations should match signature locations
 note: "-":3:5: see current operation: 
  "hw.module"() ({
  ^bb0(%arg0: i1):
    "hw.output"(%arg0) : (i1) -> ()
  }) {module_type = !hw.modty<input I : i1, output O : i1>, parameters = [], sym_name = "test"} : () -> ()
```

Now if I replace it with a dummy location that isn't unknown, e.g.

```mlir
module {
    hw.module @test(in %I: i1 loc("foo":1:3), out O: i1 loc("foo":1:3)) {
        hw.output %I : i1
    }
}
```

this seems to compile fine

```verilog
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.58.0
module test(    // -:3:5
  input  I,     // foo:1:3
  output O      // foo:1:3
);

  assign O = I; // -:4:9
endmodule
```
